creator: Martha Finley
description:
LibriVox recording of Elsie's Motherhood by Martha Finley.
Read in English by Allison; Kimberly Krause; kandice stehlik; Lynne Thompson; Bethany Baldwin; AlaynaMay; KHand; Bria Snow
In the fourth book in this classic series, Elsie is now a young woman, married and starting a young family of their own. This story is set in the few last years before the Civil War which tore apart our nation in the years 1861-1865, and continuing thereafter. (Summary by GabrielleC)
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (232MB)
